In the Matter of Antonio BONDI, Debtor. Antonio BONDI v. Walter S. BAER, Trustee. No. 5608. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Oct. 8, 1935. Blaine B. Gernon, of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Edward Sonnenschein, Henry S. Moser, Isaac E. Ferguson, and Ben I. Greenebaum, Jr., all of Chicago, Ill., for appellee.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges, and BRIGGLE, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered by the court that the motion of appellee that this appeal be dismissed be sustained. Thereupon, it is ordered, adjudged, and decreed that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed with costs.
